President Obama met with FIFA President Joseph Blatter at the White House to discuss the US bid to host the World Cup in either 2018 or 2022. President Obama praised FIFA for their efforts to incorporate community service, education, and public health projects into their plans for the 2010 World Cup in South Africa. He expressed his gratitude to Mr. Blatter for inviting him to next year's event and hoped his schedule would allow him to attend. President Obama also thanked Mr. Blatter for the soccer balls he brought as a gift for his daughters.